                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Don't think you can raise melee skills by fighting pets anymore.  Easiest way to raise offense is to damage shield yourself (banshee aura, look for it, its in your spellbook somewhere) and do a lot of tanking.<br /><br />Could do all 3 at the same time solo, find some blue undead mobs and tank them for your pet.  Good way to practice it now, cus you'll likely be doing a lot of it in the future.  :)<br /><br />For weapon and probably offense skill, just find a low delay weapon of that type.  The more times you swing, the more chances you have for a skillup.  So haste is a good thing also. :)<br /><br /><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos2/stabbingsigfull.jpg" border="0"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107355" target="_blank">Arch Lich, Innoruuk</a></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
