                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Hey, that's pretty cool about using pets to raise skills. I have some alts that need some skill work so I'll give it a shot.<br /><br />I did the skill grind with my necro when he hit 60 a while ago... Defence, piercing, 1hb were all pretty laughable and the low defence was definitely a problem.<br /><br />I raised them all to max by hitting the Grey and tanking skellies, just like a previous poster suggested. The recipe I used was pretty simple. Pull blue skelly, slow it, send in pet, Vex it, then wade in and start beatin on it. I'd throw in an occasional deflux if I got a pretty good beat-down.<br /><br />Low delay weapons help... haste too, obviously... And a dex buff if you can get it.<br /><br />Took me several hours to bring defence from 80ish to max, and weap skills from a laughable 15-30ish to max. So it can be done. Hopefully the pet duel suggestion works because I think that would be a better (safer!) way of doing it.<br /><br /><br />What trickery is this?!</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
